reviews.text: I wanted the Steak Sandwich but they were out of that item. I opted for the Meatball Sandwich and Cesar Salad. The sandwich was very tasty, the meatballs tasted homemade with a fair portion of mozzarella and tomato sauce. The salad was fresh and  tasty. I scored my dish a 5 for taste and a 4 for portion size. The facility is well decorated and big enough to host a big party. There is a small variety of beers and I assume a full bar. I did not try any deserts .

Aaron was a wonderful server. I really liked my cheese ravioli but I had a bite of my husband‚Äôs lasagna and I wish i ordered it instead.

The space has a large free parking lot that is easily accessible. It took a while to get our entrees but the appetizers and salads came out fast.

I would recommend if you‚Äôre looking for great food and great service!

We ordered delivery via Uber eats bc they had a BOGO on pasta and pizza. We tried the Tortiglioni Rosa & Margherita Pizza, which were decent, but nothing special.

The slices with fresh tomato & cheese were good, but the center of the pizza crust was pretty soggy. The light cheese wouldn't be an issue on an excellent pizza but the sauce and crust were just basic.

Pasta noodles were cooked perfectly and sausage had a nice flavor, but the peas were undercooked (I love Al dente veggies, but they were nearly raw).

We live blocks away so will give them another try in hopes it was just bad luck.

I really want to support this neighborhood spot, but my experiences have been consistently frustrating. Every online order has been met with no clear updates about the status of the food, and a few times the manager hasn‚Äôt answered the phone when I‚Äôve tried to reach out. It‚Äôs disappointing to see a place with such potential struggle with basic communication and reliability. I hope the team can tighten things up‚Äîstreamlining order updates and improving phone accessibility‚Äîbecause this neighborhood deserves a strong neighborhood spot.

Absolutely love Spasso‚Äôs!!!!  We live very close and go here all the time. It‚Äôs local, family owned and very good in all aspects of how and why you would make your decision on which restaurant to go to. So, we are very frequent visitors and will continue to do so!!!  Love it very much!!!‚Äô
